# Project: Amazon Price Drop Monitor (ECFX take-home)

## Context
- Take-home evaluation scoped to 4 hours of AI-assisted coding work.
- Evaluated on: functionality, design clarity, failure handling, data model,
  separation of concerns, AI collaboration, readability.
- MVP FIRST. Core requirements only. Stretch goals are not on the table.
- Owner prefers direct, structured output over commentary or hedging.

## MVP discipline — the single most important rule
- If a feature is not in the "Core requirements" list in PROJECT_CONTEXT.md,
  do not build it. Do not suggest building it unprompted.
- If you finish a stage early, STOP and wait for instruction. Do not
  proactively add features to fill time.
- When in doubt between "the clean version" and "the simple version,"
  pick simple. We can refactor; we cannot un-spend time.
- No premature abstraction. No "framework for future notification channels."
  Two concrete notifiers behind a Protocol is the ceiling.

